      <byline class="print_byline">By MICHAEL WINES</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Wines, Michael</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Thirty nine people die in northern Lesotho when bus carrying 103 textile workers collides with tractor-trailer truck; one or both vehicles may have been speeding (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>At least 39 people died late Monday when a bus carrying 103 textile workers collided with a tractor-trailer truck in northern Lesotho, a police spokesman said. The accident occurred while the bus, traveling between Maputsoe, a garment-making center on the South Africa border, and Fobane, a village about 15 miles south, was on a winding road. One or both vehicles may have been speeding, the police said.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL WINES</p>
      </block>
